summary: What if Jaime Lannister is the one to kill the Night King??? He’s riding North, he’ll likely bend the knee to Sansa, he’s got...
body: What if Jaime Lannister is the one to kill the Night King??? He’s riding North, he’ll likely bend the knee to Sansa, he’s got Widow’s Wail (half of Ice which is Valeryian Steel) and he is already tarnished by the nickname Kingslayer. Imagine if this is how he regains his honour, by killing another King and doing it for parallel reasons: the first, he killed to save the city from fire, the second, he kills to save the country from ice.

summary:
Sansa: What is your biggest fear?
Jon: Probably losing... and loss in general?
Jon: Also jellyfish
Arya: I don't know if this is...
body:
Sansa: What is your biggest fear?

Jon: Probably losing… and loss in general?

Jon: Also jellyfish

Arya: I don’t know if this is a fear but I’m really fascinated by the darkness that consumes you when death comes? Thinking about that split second of terror where you feel the most alone in the world? When you flash back to all the decisions you’ve ever made to that point? And realising that, like, we live our entire lives leading up to that moment?

Jon: And Arya
